<!--
	==========================================================================
	Vocation Formula & Balance Documentation
	==========================================================================

	ATTRIBUTE REFERENCE:
	  gaincap      = Capacity gained per level (carry weight)
	  gainhp       = Hit points gained per level
	  gainmana     = Mana points gained per level
	  gainhpticks  = Seconds between passive HP regeneration ticks (lower = faster)
	  gainhpamount = HP restored per regeneration tick
	  gainmanaticks = Seconds between passive mana regeneration ticks
	  gainmanaamount = Mana restored per regeneration tick
	  manamultiplier = Cost multiplier for spells (lower = cheaper spells)
	  attackspeed  = Milliseconds between melee attacks (2000 = one swing every 2s)
	  basespeed    = Base walking speed (tiles per... higher = faster)
	  soulmax      = Maximum soul points
	  gainsoulticks = Seconds to regenerate 1 soul point
	  fromvoc      = Base vocation ID this vocation promotes from

	FORMULA MULTIPLIERS (inside <formula> element):
	  meleeDamage  = Multiplier applied to melee damage output
	                 1.0 = baseline; 1.2 = 20% stronger melee; 1.3 = 30% stronger
	  distDamage   = Multiplier applied to distance weapon damage
	                 1.0 = baseline; 1.2 = 20% stronger ranged; 1.3 = 30% stronger
	  defense      = Multiplier applied to shield/defense calculations
	                 1.0 = baseline; 1.2 = 20% more effective blocking
	  armor        = Multiplier applied to armor damage reduction
	                 1.0 = baseline; 1.2 = 20% more armor mitigation

	SKILL MULTIPLIERS (inside <skill> elements):
	  Lower multiplier = faster skill advancement.
	  Skill IDs:
	    0 = Fist Fighting    1 = Club Fighting    2 = Sword Fighting
	    3 = Axe Fighting     4 = Distance Fighting  5 = Shielding
	    6 = Fishing

	BALANCE DESIGN BY VOCATION CLASS:
	  Knight (id 4/8):   High HP (15/lvl), high melee/defense/armor (1.2-1.3x),
	                     slow mana regen, expensive spells (3.0x mana cost).
	                     Fastest melee skill gain (1.1x). Tank role.
	  Archer (id 3/7):   Medium HP (10/lvl), high distance damage (1.2-1.3x),
	                     balanced mana. Fastest distance skill gain (1.1x).
	                     Ranged DPS role.
	  Mage (id 1/5):     Low HP (5/lvl), huge mana pool (30/lvl), fast mana regen,
	                     cheap spells (1.1x cost). No combat formula bonuses.
	                     Magic DPS role.
	  Druid (id 2/6):    Same HP/mana as Mage, slightly faster skill advancement
	                     (1.8x vs 2.0x for weapon skills). Healer/support role.

	  Promoted vocations (id 5-8) gain improved regen rates (+10 HP/mana per
	  tick instead of +5), doubled soul max (200), and faster soul regen.
	  Archers and Knights also receive increased formula multipliers upon
	  promotion (e.g. distDamage 1.2 -> 1.3, meleeDamage 1.2 -> 1.3).
	==========================================================================
-->
